  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for python311",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for python311 fixes the following issues:\n\nSecurity issues fixed:\n\n- CVE-2026-3446: base64 decoding stops at first padded quad by default and ignores other information that could be\n  processed (bsc#1261970).\n\nOther updates and bugfixes:\n\n- Rewrite structure of Python interpreter packages. `python3*` symbols should be now provided by real `python3`\n  packages and its subpackages instead of the virtual provides (bsc#1258364).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
